Sentencas: Layered GdBaCo2-xNixO5+delta (0 <= x <= 0.3) complex oxides were synthesized and investigated as cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Thermal expansion and electrochemical properties of Ni-doped GdBaCo2O5+δ double-perovskite type oxides

Sentencas: All compositions formed an orthorhombic double-perovskite structure after calcination at 1000 degrees C for 5 h. The thermal expansion coefficient (TEC) was effectively decreased due to the partial substitution of Ni for Co, but the cathodic polarization resistance slightly increased with the increasing Ni content.
Titulo: Thermal expansion and electrochemical properties of Ni-doped GdBaCo2O5+δ double-perovskite type oxides

Sentencas: Among the tested oxides, the GdBaCo1.7Ni0.3O5+delta composition showed a fairly reduced TEC (15.5 x 10(-6) K-1) and reasonably low polarization resistances (e.g., 0.54 Omega cm(2) at 600 degrees C), which was considered as a promising candidate for IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Thermal expansion and electrochemical properties of Ni-doped GdBaCo2O5+δ double-perovskite type oxides
